The paper focuses on learning binary vector embeddings for image and video retrieval, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed method involves optimizing mutual information in deep neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also evaluates the method on image retrieval benchmarks, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
